# SHA Family Algorithm Example in F#

Here's an example demonstrating SHA-256 hashing using the SHA family algorithms in F#:

```fsharp
open System
open System.Security.Cryptography
open System.Text

// Function to compute SHA-256 hash
let sha256Hash (input: string) : string =
    use sha256 = SHA256.Create()
    let inputBytes = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(input)
    let hashBytes = sha256.ComputeHash(inputBytes)
    // Convert byte array to hexadecimal string
    BitConverter.ToString(hashBytes).Replace("-", "").ToLowerInvariant()

// Function to compute SHA-1 hash (another SHA family algorithm)
let sha1Hash (input: string) : string =
    use sha1 = SHA1.Create()
    let inputBytes = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(input)
    let hashBytes = sha1.ComputeHash(inputBytes)
    BitConverter.ToString(hashBytes).Replace("-", "").ToLowerInvariant()

// Function to compute SHA-512 hash
let sha512Hash (input: string) : string =
    use sha512 = SHA512.Create()
    let inputBytes = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(input)
    let hashBytes = sha512.ComputeHash(inputBytes)
    BitConverter.ToString(hashBytes).Replace("-", "").ToLowerInvariant()

// Example usage
let sampleText = "Hello, World! This is a test message for SHA hashing."

printfn "Original text: %s" sampleText
printfn "SHA-256 hash:  %s" (sha256Hash sampleText)
printfn "SHA-1 hash:    %s" (sha1Hash sampleText)
printfn "SHA-512 hash:  %s" (sha512Hash sampleText)

// Example with different inputs

)
